Package seng202.group2.model.datacategories

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Categorical  
    DataClassification  
    Importable
    A simple interface used to mark DataCategory classes as being importable.
    Numerical  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Arrest
    True if the crime incident resulted in an arrest being made.
    Beat
    Police district where the crime incident occurred.
    Block
    The address of the crime incident at a city block level.
    CaseNumber
    The case number associated with the crime record in the police database.
    DataCategory
    This class facilitates the selection of the various categories within a CrimeRecord, providing the methods setCategoryValue and getCategoryValue for setting and getting the value of an attribute of a CrimeRecord instance through the corresponding DataCategory.
    Date
    The date and time at which the crime incident occurred.
    Domestic
    True if the crime incident was classified as domestic.
    FBICode
    FBI crime code assigned to the crime incident.
    ID
    The ID associated with the crime record in the police database.
    IUCRCode
    Illinois Uniform Crime Reporting code.
    IUCRCodeDictionary
    A dictionary of Illinois Crime Reporting Codes and their meanings.
    Latitude
    The latitudinal location where the crime incident occurred.
    LocationDescription
    A textual description of the location where the crime incident occurred.
    Longitude
    The longitudinal location where the crime incident occurred.
    PrimaryDescription
    A textual description of the type of the crime incident.
    SecondaryDescription
    A textual description giving more details supplementing the categorization of the crime type provided in the primary description.
    Ward
    Election precinct where the crime incident occurred.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UnsupportedCategoryException
    This exception type is thrown when a process tries to perform an operation on or using data from a category that is unsupported, or when trying to add data to an attribute corresponding to a DataCategory which is unsupported or does not exist.
